<div class="project-text">
    <h3>The Project</h3>
    <p>The very first project I worked on with Nello Russo, my mentor. It is how we met, and how I learned the first basics of working in an agency. I remember feeling nervous about it, not knowing that a mountain of far more complex and vaguely briefed projects was on the way. In retrospect this one was straightforward.</p>
    <p>An advertising page for online newspapers, presenting a watchmaking company from the island of Elba. We used diagonal separators to reference the cuts and facets of Locman watch crystals, and paired that with a photography set that worked beautifully in a dark, low-key mood. A strong contrast against the light pages of news sites, while keeping the type readable and understated, because a luxury brand does not need to shout.</p>
    <p>Nello is now at <a href="https://pressato.it/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Pressato Coffee and Books</a> and at <a href="https://nellorusso.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">nellorusso.com</a>.</p>
